<%= vars.product_full %> Management Console provides a unified installation experience for deploying <%= vars.product_short %> to vSphere. The management console is provided as a virtual appliance that you deploy to vSphere by using an OVA template. The management console provides a graphical user interface that assists you with configuration when deploying <%= vars.product_short %> to vSphere: 

- Configures the chosen network for <%= vars.product_short %>
- Deploys Ops Manager v2.4.5
- Generates and registers SSL certificates
- Deploys BOSH Director v2.3
- Deploys Enterprise PKS v1.5.0
- Deploys Harbor Registry v1.7.5

<%= vars.product_short %> Management Console is easy to use. If you are experienced with installing <%= vars.product_short %> on vSphere, this document and the tool tips and help in the installer UI should be enough to complete the process. If you are new to <%= vars.product_short %>, refer to this documentation as needed to assist with the installation.

After you have deployed <%= vars.product_short %> on vSphere, you can use the management console to monitor and manage the operation of your <%= vars.product_short %> deployments, as well as perform upgrades and patch the individual components.